Quickstart
==========

Install all necessary packages and headers, for Debian this should be sufficient:

    apt-get install libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev zlib1g-dev build-essential python-dev libssl1.0.0 libffi-dev libssl-dev python-psycopg2 libpq-dev python-virtualenv libjpeg-dev zlib1g-dev

Then install everything with:

    mkdir storedir
    cd storedir
    virtualenv venv
    . venv/bin/activate
    git clone git@github.com:xenim/xenim_frontend_project.git
    cd xenim_frontend_project
    pip install -r requirements-dev.txt

Configuration
-------------

Settings are stored in classes in settings/. See settings/example_local.py on how 
add local settings (databases, etc). For a start it is needed to create base_local.py
and configure SECRET_KEY.

Run with integrated webserver
-----------------------------

    python manage.py runserver --configuration=DevWWWSettings
